, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Stanley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Stanley, including those in Yorkshire, Staffordshire, Derbyshire, Durham, Gloucestershire, and Wiltshire, named with Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. This English name has been established in Ireland since the 13th century where it was Gaelicized as <b>de Stainléigh</b>.","English: possibly also a variant of <b>Stoneley</b>, a habitational name from Stoneley Green in Burland (Cheshire), Stoneleigh (Warwickshire), or Stonely in Kimbolton (Huntingdonshire), all named with Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Americanized form of any of various like-sounding names in other languages, for example Polish   Stanislawski  , Greek   Anastasiou  , and Serbian <b>Stojadinov</b> (patronymic from the personal name <i>Stojadin</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Stanislawski","meanings":["Polish (<b>Stanisławski</b>): habitational name for someone from any of various places called Stanisław, Stanisławów, or Stanisławice, named with the personal name <i>Stanisław</i> (see   Stanislav  )."]},{"name":"Standley","meanings":["English: variant of   Stanley  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry De Stanley was born in 1025, in Normandy, France. He married Mrs Henry De Stanley in 1049, in Normandy, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1025–":"1025–Surnud","1030–Female":"1030–Surnud","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1025–Male":"1025–Surnud","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","9 May 1050":"9. mai 1050","Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, England","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1025–":"1025–Kuollut","1030–Female":"1030–Kuollut","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1025–Male":"1025–Kuollut","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","9 May 1050":"9. toukokuuta 1050","Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, England","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1025–":"1025–Décédé","1030–Female":"1030–Décédée","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1025–Male":"1025–Décédé","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1130":"1130","1030":"1030","1050":"1050","9 May 1050":"9 mai 1050","Balterley, Staffordshire, England":"Balterley, Staffordshire, Angleterre","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Henry De Stanley est né en 1025, à Normandie, France. Il a épousé Mrs Henry De Stanley en 1049, à Normandie, France. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1025–":"1025–Verstorben","1030–Female":"1030–Verstorben","1050–1130":"1050–1130","1025–Male":"1025–Verstorben","1049":"1049","1025":"1025","1130":"1130","1030":"1030"